-- Italian Banks Reject Severstal's Debt Plan for Lucchini, Messaggero Says
-- Sonia Sirletti
-- 2010-09-07T06:06:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-07/italian-banks-reject-severstal-s-debt-plan-for-lucchini-messaggero-says.html

          
          
             Banks including Monte dei Paschi di
Siena SpA and UniCredit SpA rejected a proposal by  Severstal OAO 
Chief Executive Officer  Alexei Mordashov  to wipe out some of
Italian unit Lucchini SpAâ€™s debt, daily Il  Messaggero  said.  
 Lucchini owes creditors 770 million euros ($986 million).
Mordashov plans to inject 50 million euros into the unit through
a capital increase, Messaggero reported, without saying where it
got the information.  
